ğŸ“¦ Example with all 4:
java
Copy
Edit
public class Demo {
    private int a = 10;
    int b = 20;               // default
    protected int c = 30;
    public int d = 40;

    public void show() {
        System.out.println(a + " " + b + " " + c + " " + d);
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo obj = new Demo();
        // System.out.println(obj.a); âŒ private
        System.out.println(obj.b);     // âœ… default
        System.out.println(obj.c);     // âœ… protected
        System.out.println(obj.d);     // âœ… public
    }
}
(Assuming Test is in same package)

âœ… Best Practices:
Scenario	Use this modifier
Sensitive info (password, pin)	private
API methods, global use	public
Extendable but safe methods	protected
Internal helper classes	default (no modifier)
ğŸ¯ Interview Tip:
Q: What's the difference between private and protected?
ğŸ§  A:

private = only within class

protected = within package + subclass (even in different package)

